# Hall Pass — Environment Setup

## Supabase Configuration

1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
2. Run the schema.sql file in the SQL Editor
3. Copy your project credentials

## Required Environment Variables

### Mobile App (.env.local)
```
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key
```

### Web App (.env.local)
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key
NEXT_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_WEB_KEY=rcb_your_web_key
```

### Backend (Edge Functions)
```
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
REVENUECAT_API_KEY=your-revenuecat-key
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_... (for web payments)
```

## RevenueCat Setup

1. Create a RevenueCat account at https://revenuecat.com
2. Create a new app for Hall Pass
3. Add products matching the IDs in packages/iap-core/src/config.ts
4. Copy API keys to your environment variables

## iOS/Android Store Setup

### iOS App Store
- Bundle ID: com.hallpass.game
- Configure in-app purchases in App Store Connect
- Add products matching the IDs in config.ts

### Android Play Store
- Package: com.hallpass.game
- Configure in-app products in Google Play Console
- Add products matching the IDs in config.ts

## Running the Apps

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run mobile app
cd apps/mobile
npm run ios     # iOS simulator
npm run android # Android emulator

# Run web app
cd apps/web
npm run dev     # localhost:3000
```
